<s> I think we again have to go back to function.  </s>
<s> As I understand it... If the function of the dotted line you mentioned is to divide two blocks of text -- then it does need an alt text and the alt text should be "divider line" or some such.  </s>
<s> It should not describe what the line looks like ('e.g. dotted line") but rather its function.  </s>
<s> If a graphic is on the page to confirm to the viewer that they got to the right page... and the page already has a title -- then it may not have an additional function.  </s>
<s> But if it is to show how nice a place it is -- then it does have a function - and that function should be provided in text.  </s>
<s> You do not need to describe every little detail in the picture.  </s>
<s> (e.g. if it is a picture of the town you don't have to describe the number of buildings, what they look like, the street sign, etc. etc. unless some part of that is critical to the function of the town.  </s>
<s> E.g. could any other picture of another part of the town have been used instead.)  </s>
<s> In general I would think the safer thing to do is to provide short alt text of pictures rather than decide that they have no function.  </s>
<s> It is rarely true.  </s>
